A clean-water advocate took an Earth Day swim in New York City 's polluted Gowanus Canal , a site designated by the federal government , but quit .
Christopher Swain wore a protective yellow suit as he went over a railing and into the water around 2 pm Wednesday in Brooklyn but completed only two-thirds of a mile of the 1.8-mile waterway .
He swam into the canal in a stunt to urge environmental clean up .
